File Management:

Create a workspace:

mkdir -p ~/linux-labs/week1
cd ~/linux-labs/week1

mkdir docs images backup
touch docs/file{1..5}.txt


Tasks
List all files in long format.   --> ls -l
Show hidden files.   ----> ls -la
Copy all files from docs to backup.  ---->  cp -r docs/* backup/
Rename file1.txt to notes.txt.  ---->  mv /docs/file1.txt /docs/notes.txt
Remove file5.txt. ----> rm -rf file5.txt
Count files inside docs. ----> find . -type f | wc -l       or     ls docs/ | wc -l